# Project Spec: Kata Portfolio Website

## Objective

Build a minimalist, artwork-first portfolio website for an illustrator.

The homepage focuses on visual exploration using a masonry grid of artworks.
Projects exist as secondary narrative layers that users can choose to open.

The system must support:

- CMS-driven content via Supabase
- instant content updates (no redeploy)
- clean, professional, minimal design
- scalable frontend architecture

This is a production-grade portfolio, not an experiment.

---

## Design Direction (FIXED)

The design direction is already defined another md file and must NOT be changed.

---

## Tech Stack

### Frontend

- React (Vite)
- JavaScript
- Tailwind CSS

### Backend / CMS

- Supabase (database + auth)
- No custom backend
- No admin panel inside the site

### Hosting

- GitHub (source control)
- Vercel (deployment)

---

## Data Flow (IMPORTANT)

- Homepage loads published artworks only
- Filtering is done by artwork.category
- Clicking artwork opens fullscreen overlay
- Overlay supports horizontal scrolling between artworks
- â€œView projectâ€ navigates to project detail page
- Project page loads project + its artworks
- Content updates appear instantly (no redeploy)

---

## Security & Access

- Public frontend uses Supabase anon key
- RLS enforces published-only visibility
- No secrets exposed
- No write access from frontend
- Content edited only via Supabase Studio

---

## Commands

- Dev: `npm run dev`
- Build: `npm run build`
- Preview: `npm run preview`

---

## Project Structure (recommended)

- `src/`
  - `components/`
  - `pages/`
  - `layouts/`
  - `hooks/`
  - `services/` (Supabase queries)
  - `styles/`
- `docs/`
- `public/`

